          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bulk ferment",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the {{plain-flour}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{sea-salt-fine}} and {{yeast-fast-action}} in a stand-mixer bowl. Add lukewarm {{whole-milk}}, softened first {{unsalted-butter}} and the first {{eggs}}. Mix on low for 7 minutes to a soft, smooth dough. Bulk ferment in an oiled bowl at room temperature for 1 hour until doubled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll, fill, slice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Knock back the dough and roll on a floured surface to a 40×30 cm rectangle. Spread evenly with the softened second {{unsalted-butter}}. Scatter the {{soft-brown-sugar}} and {{mixed-spice}} across, then the {{dried-currants}} and {{mixed-peel}}. From a long edge, roll up tightly into a sausage. Slice into 12 pieces with a sharp knife. Set cut-side-up in the lined square tin, 4 across and 3 down, with a small gap between each. They will spread and meet.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Proof, bake, glaze hot",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Proof in the warm for 90 minutes until visibly puffed and the buns are touching. Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Bake for 22 to 25 minutes; the tops should be deep gold and the buns should sound hollow when tapped on top. While the buns bake, dissolve the second {{caster-sugar}} in the {{water}} in a small pan over a low heat and bring to a simmer for 2 minutes. As soon as the buns come out, brush the sugar syrup generously over the tops. Cool 10 minutes in the tin before lifting out.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
